description.narrative:
3.	Protection of vulnerable groups.
•	Relief support provided with priority given to people with destroyed houses and/or deceased family members, particularly women, orphans, elderly and disabled;
•	Empowerment of the large proportion of women with immediate source of income, hope and dignity through working for the temporary homes for their families and children.

4.	Provision of life-saving relief management and humanitarian support monitored, reported and evaluated.
•	Monitoring on CERF life-saving relief support conducted;
•	An evaluation report will be produced with documentation of experiences and lessons learned.
